#   Last push  : 2026-06-02
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   daslang (formerly daScript / "das") is Gaijin Entertainment's
#   internal scripting language, written to solve a real problem
#   in their ECS game engine:  interop overhead between Lua /
#   Squirrel scripting and C++ was eating the per-frame budget,
#   so they built a language whose data layout matches C++
#   exactly — *no* marshaling, *no* boxing, *no* conversion;
#   script↔C++ calls are near-zero-cost.  Three execution tiers,
#   all planned from day one:
#     1) fast tree-based interpreter,
#     2) AOT compilation to C++ (required for consoles), and
#     3) JIT via LLVM with a per-script DLL cache.
#   Hybrid mode uses semantic hashing — unchanged functions stay
#   AOT-compiled, changed ones fall back to the interpreter —
#   so a production game can ship a hotfix without a full
#   rebuild.  Iteration target is "full production game
#   recompiles in ~5 seconds; hot reload built in".
#
#   The compiler is a single multi-mode driver: invoke it with
#   one or more `.das` source files to run the interpreter, with
#   `-aot` for AOT C++ codegen, with `-jit` for JIT execution,
#   with `-exe` for self-contained JIT-to-executable bundling,
#   with `-run-fmt` to drive the formatter (`das-fmt`), with the
#   `daspkg` package manager script for install/search.  Project
#   files use a `.das_project` build manifest that lists module
#   roots; dynamic modules use a `.das_module` per-folder
#   manifest.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from utils/daScript/main.cpp
#                       help banner + argument parser in
#                       `das_main` and `das_aot_main`; extracted
#                       via `gh api repos/GaijinEntertainment/
#                       daScript/contents/utils/daScript/
#                       main.cpp`)
#
#   daslang [SCRIPT.das...] [-main <FN>] [-log] [-pause] [...]
#           [-- <SCRIPT_ARGS>...]
#   daslang -aot <IN.das> <OUT.das.cpp> [-q] [-p] [...]
#   daslang -jit <SCRIPT.das> [...]
#   daslang -exe <SCRIPT.das> -output <PATH> [...]
#
#   Help / version:
#     --version, -version            Print daslang version and
#                                    exit
#
#   Entry / mode:
#     -main <FN_NAME>                Set entry function name
#                                    [default: main]
#     -jit                           Enable Just-In-Time
#                                    compilation
#     -jit-no-cache                  With -jit: skip the per-
#                                    script DLL cache, codegen
#                                    direct in-memory  (useful
#                                    when `.jitted_scripts/` is
#                                    stale or unwanted)
#     -exe                           JIT compile to standalone
#                                    executable  (implies
#                                    -dry-run)
#     -output <PATH>                 Set JIT output path
#     -aot <IN> <OUT>                AOT compile <IN.das> to
#                                    <OUT.das.cpp>
#     -aotlib                        Like -aot but build an AOT
#                                    library
#     -use-aot                       Enable AOT linking
#                                    (requires AOT stubs linked
#                                    into the binary)
#     -aot-macros                    AOT compile macros too
#                                    (export_all + larger stack)
#     -run-fmt <-i|-d> <-v2|-v1> [--semicolon]
#                                    Run the formatter (das-fmt)
#                                    over the input
#
#   Project:
#     -project <PATH.das_project>    Path to project file
#     -project_root <PATH>           Root directory of the
#                                    project  (used for dynamic
#                                    modules)
#     -load_module <PATH>            Directly load a single
#                                    dynamic-module folder (the
#                                    one containing
#                                    `.das_module`);  repeatable.
#                                    Bypasses the
#                                    `project_root/modules/<name>`
#                                    scan and shadows same-
#                                    basename entries from
#                                    dasroot/project_root
#     -dasroot <PATH>                Set path to daslang root
#                                    folder (with daslib)
#
#   Syntax modes:
#     -v2syntax                      Enable version 2 syntax
#                                    (braces `{}` for code
#                                    blocks)  [default]
#     -v1syntax                      Enable version 1 syntax
#                                    (Python-style indentation
#                                    for code blocks)
#     -v2makeSyntax                  Enable v1 syntax with v2
#                                    constructor syntax (for
#                                    arrays / structures)
#
#   Diagnostics / debugging:
#     -log                           Output program code
#     -log-compile-time              Log per-module compile-time
#                                    breakdown (parse / infer
#                                    with pass count / optimize
#                                    / macro / simulate) +
#                                    function count
#     -pause                         Pause after errors AND again
#                                    before exiting
#     -dry-run                       Compile + simulate without
#                                    execution
#     -compile-only                  Compile without simulate +
#                                    execute
#     -cross-platform                AOT cross-platform mode
#                                    (with -aot)
#     -no-dynamic-modules            Skip loading dynamic modules
#     -no-lint                       Skip the lint pass
#                                    (Program::lint)
#     -q                             Quiet
#     --linear-stack-allocator       Disable scoped stack
#                                    allocator
#     --no-dump-leaks                Silence JobStatus +
#                                    HandleRegistry + smart_ptr
#                                    leak dumps at exit
#                                    (default: dump)
#     --das-wait-debugger            Wait for debugger to attach
#
#   Profiler / tracking:
#     --das-profiler                 Enable profiler
#     --das-profiler-log-file <PATH>
#                                    Set profiler log file
#     --das-profiler-manual          Manual profiler control
#     --das-profiler-memory          Memory profiler
#     --das-profiler-time-unit <U>   Time unit for profiler
#                                    output (ns | us | ms | s)
#     --das-profiler-thread-local    Per-thread profiler agent
#                                    (default when not tracking
#                                    memory)
#     --das-profiler-global          Singleton profiler agent
#                                    (default with
#                                    --das-profiler-memory)
#     --das-profiler-leaks           Track live heap allocations
#                                    and dump leaks on context
#                                    destroy
#     --track-smart-ptr <ID>         Track smart pointer with id
#     --track-job-status <ID>        Track JobStatus / Channel /
#                                    LockBox with id
#
#   Standalone-executable bundling  (with -exe):
#     --list-shared-modules <PATH>   Write JSON describing the
#                                    program's shared modules
#                                    and daspkg-package `.das`
#                                    module sources to <PATH>
#     --force-shared-module <NAME>   Force-include a shared
#                                    module by daslang or
#                                    package name  (repeatable)
#
#   Argument separator:
#     --                             Separator between daslang
#                                    flags and `script-args`
#                                    arguments passed to the
#                                    script's `main()`
#
# LANGUAGE-CORPUS POSITION
#   daslang is the 180th programming language entry in this
#   completion corpus — a round-number 180th-language milestone.
#   It joins Blaise (R988 179th), Fusion (R984 178th), Aver
