#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/GaijinEntertainment/daScript/contents/
#         README.md
#       → "Daslang (formerly daScript) is a high-performance,
#          statically typed programming language built for games
#          and real-time applications."
#       → AOT/JIT/interp three-tier execution model
#       → ./bin/daslang -aot main.das aot_main.cpp
#       → ./bin/daslang -jit main.das
#     gh api repos/GaijinEntertainment/daScript/contents/utils/
#         daScript/main.cpp
#       → static usage banner lists every flag verbatim
#       → das_main entry-point + das_aot_main entry-point parse
#         `-q`, `-aot`, `-aotlib`, `-p`, `-dry-run`,
#         `-das-mode`, `-cross-platform`, `-aot-macros`,
#         `-project`, `-dasroot`, `-project-root`/-project_root,
#         `-load-module`/-load_module, `-v2syntax`, `-v1syntax`,
